Definition: having undesirable or negative qualities
Example: a bad report card; his sloppy appearance made a bad impression; a bad little boy; clothes in bad shape; a bad cut; bad luck; the news was very bad; the reviews were bad; the pay is bad; it was a bad light for reading; the movie was a bad choice
Synonyms: noun, attribute, badness, GOOD, DISOBEDIENT, EVIL, UNFAVORABLE, WORSE, WORST, quality, having, undesirable, or, negative, qualities, a, bad, report, card, his, sloppy, appearance, made, impression, little, boy, clothes, in, shape, cut, luck, the, news, was, very, reviews, were, pay, is, it, light, for, reading, movie, choice
Category: adj.all
